<DOC><DOCNO> AP881212-0071 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-12-12-88 1015EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-MilitarySanta     12-12 0158</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Military Santa,0162</SECOND><HEAD>Santa Appears From A Military Helicopter</HEAD><DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Residents of a town southwest of Tokyo got a doublesurprise when a U.S. military helicopter made an emergency landingwith Santa Claus aboard.   Police said today the Navy helicopter landed Sunday in a ricepaddy about 220 yards from an elementary school after an oil leakwas detected in the rotor.   One of the four crew members emerged from the helicopter dressedin a Santa Claus suit in hopes of surprising his family at nearbyAtsugi Naval Base, said the police officer in Isehara, 30 milessouthwest of Tokyo.   ``(The crew member) said he boarded the helicopter in uniform andchanged while he was aboard,'' said the police official, spoke oncondition of anonymity.   He said the helicopter was on a routine training flight and noinjuries or damage to the craft were reported. He refused to nameany of the helicopter crew members.</TEXT></DOC>